Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When David Rumenel was born about 1129, in High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England, his father, Robert Rumenel, was 36 and his mother, Mrs. Rumenel, was 31. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Rumenel. He died about 1200, in Buckinghamshire, England, at the age of 73."},"et":{"about 1129–about 1200":"umbes 1129–umbes 1200","1129–1200":"1129–1200","1136–Female":"1136–Surnud","1159–1204":"1159–1204","1095–Male":"1095–Surnud","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","1129":"1129","1204":"1204","1159":"1159","about 1129":"umbes 1129","1136":"1136","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","about 1159":"umbes 1159","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1095":"1095","before 1129":"enne 1129","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Aston Mullens, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1129–about 1200":"noin 1129–noin 1200","1129–1200":"1129–1200","1136–Female":"1136–Kuollut","1159–1204":"1159–1204","1095–Male":"1095–Kuollut","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut","1129":"1129","1204":"1204","1159":"1159","about 1129":"noin 1129","1136":"1136","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","about 1159":"noin 1159","about 1200":"noin 1200","1095":"1095","before 1129":"ennen vuotta 1129","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Aston Mullens, Bucki